f=Brand Studio/atlas/operational/commands/atlas-commands.md · p=Routing reference atlas: phrase skill, plus precedence overlapping "brand/design" vocabulary. · h2:Trigger Table=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · h2:Trigger Table=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Trigger Table=\| brand-guidelines \| "on brand check," "is this on brand," "visual identity check," "audit this asset" \| `/atlas-audit` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| brand-identity \| "design our logo/brand," "build a visual identity," "brand colors/typography," "we don't have a brand yet" \| `/atlas-create` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| multi-brand-system \| "cross brand visual," "brand separation," "does this look like [sibling]" \| `/atlas-separate` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| layout-composition \| "layout this," "visual hierarchy," "why does this feel crowded/off," "where does the CTA go" \| `/atlas-layout` \| · h3:"Brand check" audit create=kit exists target brand brand-guidelines. none exists audit's Phase-1 stop offers fork: fill template (identity exists, undocumented) run brand-identity (no identity yet). Never audit memory. · h3:Audits in multi-brand businesses=Any `/atlas-audit` operator runs brands automatically includes multi-brand-system separation check; single-brand deployments skip documented no-op. · h3:"Design this" identity layout=System-level (logo, palette, type system) brand-identity. Artifact-level (this page, graphic) layout-composition, brand-guidelines audit after. · h3:What atlas take=Copy, tone, message content lena., Producing asset batches pixel (which calls atlas's audit QA)., Final outbound approval spark's coherence gate; atlas's PASS input it, substitute., Kit/matrix amendments operator (spark advises drift). · f=clear match ask whether need create, audit, separate, compose.